kb_used.fo:
vocabulary V {
  type Person
  type Estate
  leaves_other_heirs: Person -> Bool
  leaves_no_heirs: Person -> Bool
  is_surviving_spouse_of: Person * Person -> Bool
  is_estate_of: Estate * Person -> Bool
  acquires_full_ownership_of: Person * Estate -> Bool
}

theory T:V {
  ! spouse in Person, deceased in Person, estate in Estate: ((is_surviving_spouse_of(spouse,deceased)) & (is_estate_of(estate,deceased)) & ((leaves_other_heirs(deceased)) | (leaves_no_heirs(deceased)))) => ((acquires_full_ownership_of(spouse,estate))).
}

pipeline.extraction_prompt:
You are debugging a legal extraction failure.

Given KB_SCHEMA, CASE, and QUESTION, identify the likely generic cause of failure.
Focus on schema mismatch, missing observable facts, wrong argument order, wrong entity type, selected observable instead of derived predicate, or unsupported query shape.

Do not invent new law-specific fixes.
Return concise bullet points and one generic repair suggestion.

